<div type="edition" xml:lang="tel-Latn" rendition="class:telugu maturity:vernacular">

<p>
<lb n="1"/>śrījāyājaghanasthalīlalitakāṁcīnūtnaratnāṁku
<lb n="2" break="no"/>rō dēvaśśītamayūkhavaṁśatilaka<supplied reason="omitted">ḥ</supplied> śrīkubjaviṣṇurnṛpaḥ <g ref="sym:bar" type="punctuation">.</g>
<lb n="3"/>yatkīrtti pravijṛṁbhitē diśi diśi krīḍaccakōravrajē
<lb n="4"/>jyōtsnāśaṁkidaladviguṁjadalayō bhāṁtyuccakaiḥ kairavāḥ [<g ref="sym:doubleBar" type="punctuation">.</g> 1*]
<lb n="5"/>Āsīccaturtādhipavaṁśakarttā harttā dvi<unclear>ṣā</unclear>ṁ vēdavidāṁ ca
<lb n="6"/>bharttā <supplied reason="undefined"><g ref="sym:bar" type="punctuation">.</g></supplied> śrībuddhavarmmā kṛtapuṇyakarmmā prasphītaśarmmā ni
<lb n="7" break="no"/>janāthavarmmā [<g ref="sym:doubleBar" type="punctuation">.</g> 2*] bhṛtyakṛtyavinayēna raṁjayannaṁjunē
<lb n="8" break="no"/>ya Iva rāvaṇacchidaṁ <supplied reason="undefined"><g ref="sym:bar" type="punctuation">.</g></supplied> vainatēya Iva cakṛṇaṁcca taṁ sā
<lb n="9" break="no"/>rvvabhaumatilakaṁ sa sēvatē [<g ref="sym:doubleBar" type="punctuation">.</g> 3*] giripratīcīnnijarājalā
<lb n="10" break="no"/>ṁccanaistrisaptatigrāmavatīmmahī(ṁ)patiḥ <supplied reason="undefined"><g ref="sym:bar" type="punctuation">.</g></supplied> patiprasādō
<lb n="11" break="no"/>panatānnatāhitassa pālayāmāsa vilāsavāsavaḥ
<lb n="12"/>[<g ref="sym:doubleBar" type="punctuation">.</g> 4*] vaṁśakartṛṣu gatēṣu kēṣucittatkulādajani maṁḍabhū
<lb n="13" break="no"/>patiḥ <supplied reason="undefined"><g ref="sym:bar" type="punctuation">.</g></supplied> maṁḍanādajani gaṁḍabhū<supplied reason="omitted">pa</supplied>tirggaṁḍanādajani ma
<lb n="14" break="no"/>ṁḍabhūpatiḥ [<g ref="sym:doubleBar" type="punctuation">.</g> 5*] mēghāḍaṁbara<unclear>maṁ</unclear>barē jalamucā<note n="215-4">The rest of the inscription on this face of the pillar is lost. The record some missing lines, in No. 691 below.</note> 
</p>

